    <!--lions-->
    <h1>Lions</h1>
    <p>The lion is a wild animal and is often called “the king of the jungle.”
It lives mainly in Africa, in grasslands and savannas.
<br>
Lions are strong and powerful animals.
Male lions have a big mane, while females do not.</p>
<img src="lions.img.jpg">
<!--kangoroos-->
<h1>kangoroos</h1>
<p>The kangaroo is a wild animal.
It lives in Australia.
<br>
Kangaroos are marsupials, which means the female has a pouch to carry her baby.
The baby kangaroo is called a joey.</p>
<img src="kangoru.img.jpg">
<!--tiger-->
<h1>tiger</h1>
<p>TThe tiger is a big wild cat that lives mainly in Asia.
<br>
Tigers have orange fur with black stripes, which helps them hide in the forest.
<br>
They are carnivores, which means they eat meat like deer and wild pigs.
<br>
Tigers usually live alone and are very strong hunters.</p>
